HEADWORD: Powdered
<hw>Pow"dered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Reduced
to a powder; sprinkled with, or as with, powder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sprinkled with salt; salted; corned.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Powdered</qex> beef, pickled meats.</q>
<rj><qau>Harvey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Sem⟦eacute⟧</er>.</def> <rj><au>Walpole.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Powderflask</ent>⟦br⟧
